main event: A white, round object was observed at a five degree elevation off the horizon in Twenty-Nine Palms, California on May 6, 1955.
interesting points: The object appeared to hang in the sky and then disappear from the observer's view.
The observer estimated the object was approximately 3 feet in diameter.
After checking astronomical charts, it was determined the object could not have been any celestial body or other astronomical object.
There were other indications of unusual aerial activity in the area, according to a report made by the AFOSR squadron.
Despite the unusual activity, the description of the sighting, including the weather conditions, led to the conclusion that the sighting was probably a balloon.
